Masa, hun...none of the cleric epic stuff is a long camp.  Begurgle was the longest camp for me, next to Ragefire, and he's the first step.  If you ain't go the willpower to play in the water for a few hours while ya wait for the gob, you don't even need to think about yer epic cuz that Rage camp is gonna kick yer arse.  Pretty much all that's left after the Gurgler for anything resembling a &quot;camp&quot; is the gob in SolA, and he's spawns fairly fast from what I remember.  The rest is all triggered.  <br>
<br>
The cleric epic is too simple to get, plain and simple.  You got very few mobs to actually kill, plan a mad rush into chardok for the king, then make sure ya got the Pixie Sticks and Jolt cola within an arms reach cuz yer gonna need the sugar rush and caffeine fix to sit there waiting on Rage.  The fact that the epic is so easy to do up to Ragefire is the reason you have the bottleneck.  One cleric is campin Ragefire, and in the time this guy is waitin on Zordak to spawn, 5 other clerics have ran through all the parts for their Wakarez(tm) up to this point.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I ramble...Pala, you put a lotta thought into it.  It's a good plan.  But we all know that the first time 1 guild decided to use that method, some other guild will roll on in and whack Rage.  It's just the nature of the beast.  Guilds want their Wakarez's(tm). <br>
